### REST Client File for VS Code
### Install "REST Client" extension to run these natively or use Postman.
### Change the token and inputs dynamically as you test.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000

# ─── Auth Flow ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Register a new user
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test User",
  "email": "tester@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### 2. Login (This issues a JWT and HTTP-only refresh token)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "tester@example.com",
  "password": "Password123!"
}

### Save accessToken from login response and assign it manually or copy it:
@token = {{login.response.body.data.accessToken}}

# ─── Page Management ───────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3. Create a Draft Page
# @name createPage
POST {{baseUrl}}/pages
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "My Super AI SaaS",
  "slug": "ai-saas-demo"
}

@pageId = {{createPage.response.body.data.page._id}}

# ─── AI Generation ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 4. Generate AI Content & Map to the page
### NOTE: Requires a valid OPENAI_API_KEY in your .env file
POST {{baseUrl}}/ai/generate
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pageId": "{{pageId}}",
  "businessName": "PageCraft Competitor",
  "industry": "Marketing SaaS",
  "pageType": "Waitlist",
  "targetAudience": "Marketers & Founders",
  "ctaText": "Get Early Access",
  "designUrl": "https://app.figr.design/artifacts/a047b29c-4dd2-4590-b350-0c20a0be821a"
}

# ─── Publishing & Lead Capture ──────────────────────────────────────────

### 5. Publish the Page
POST {{baseUrl}}/pages/{{pageId}}/publish
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subdomain": "saas-launch"
}

### 6. View the Public Page via Subdomain
GET {{baseUrl}}/p/domain/saas-launch.localhost


### 7. Capture a lead automatically on the public page
POST {{baseUrl}}/pages/{{pageId}}/leads
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "email": "jane@earlyadopter.com",
  "message": "Can't wait!"
}

# ─── Analytics ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 8. Fetch Dashboard Stats (Views, Conversions, Draft counts)
GET {{baseUrl}}/user/dashboard
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Download Leads CSV (Open this link in browser normally)
GET {{baseUrl}}/pages/{{pageId}}/export-leads
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
